                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.16,
                                "byte_start": 103483,
                                "byte_stop": 132218,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has the opinion of the Court today in 10-6549, Reynolds versus United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 7.16,
                                "stop": 10.132,
                                "byte_start": 132218,
                                "byte_stop": 144025,
                                "text": "I will announce the opinion for him."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 10.132,
                                "stop": 27.234,
                                "byte_start": 144025,
                                "byte_stop": 212466,
                                "text": "The federal Sex Offender Registration and Notification Act requires those convicted of certain sex-related crimes to provide state governments with information such as names and current addresses for inclusion on state and federal sex offender registries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.234,
                                "stop": 46.571,
                                "byte_start": 212466,
                                "byte_stop": 289788,
                                "text": "The Act includes pre-Act offenders among those whom it regulates, but it also says that the \u0022Attorney General shall have the authority to specify the applicability of the Act\u0027s registration requirements to sex offenders convicted before its enactment.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.571,
                                "stop": 59.918,
                                "byte_start": 289788,
                                "byte_stop": 343183,
                                "text": "The basic question before us arises out of facts and circumstances that are complex, but for purposes of this exposition, we can simplify the context with the following hypothetical."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.918,
                                "stop": 64.556,
                                "byte_start": 343183,
                                "byte_stop": 361782,
                                "text": "A defendant is convicted of a sex crime before the Act becomes law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.556,
                                "stop": 66.543,
                                "byte_start": 361782,
                                "byte_stop": 369723,
                                "text": "The Act then becomes law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.543,
                                "stop": 70.84,
                                "byte_start": 369723,
                                "byte_stop": 386859,
                                "text": "The defendant subsequently fails to carry out the Act\u0027s requirements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.84,
                                "stop": 82.568,
                                "byte_start": 386859,
                                "byte_stop": 433775,
                                "text": "All of this takes place before the Attorney General has issued a rule that specifies that the Act applies to pre-Act offenders such as the defendant before us."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.568,
                                "stop": 102.163,
                                "byte_start": 433775,
                                "byte_stop": 512143,
                                "text": "These facts raise a legal question of whether the Act\u0027s requirement apply to pre-Act offenders who failed to comply with the Act\u0027s requirements in the period after the Act became law, but before the Attorney General validly specify the applicability of the Act to pre-Act offenders."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.163,
                                "stop": 108.649,
                                "byte_start": 512143,
                                "byte_stop": 538161,
                                "text": "We conclude that the Act\u0027s requirements do not apply to this group of pre-Act offenders."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.649,
                                "stop": 112.585,
                                "byte_start": 538161,
                                "byte_stop": 553834,
                                "text": "Our conclusion rests in part upon the language of the statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.585,
                                "stop": 125.178,
                                "byte_start": 553834,
                                "byte_stop": 604198,
                                "text": "We also note that a contrary reading will create uncertainties about just how the statute applies to pre-Act offenders, uncertainties that the Attorney General would be well suited to resolve."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.178,
                                "stop": 130.429,
                                "byte_start": 604198,
                                "byte_stop": 625201,
                                "text": "And we explain how our reading likely furthers various practical congressional objectives."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.429,
                                "stop": 134.025,
                                "byte_start": 625201,
                                "byte_stop": 639620,
                                "text": "Our opinion discusses these and related matters."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.025,
                                "stop": 146.26,
                                "byte_start": 639620,
                                "byte_stop": 688626,
                                "text": "Now, as noted we hold that the relevant statutory requirements do not apply to pre-Act offenders prior to the time the Attorney General issued valid regulations specifying their applicability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.26,
                                "stop": 150.52,
                                "byte_start": 688626,
                                "byte_stop": 705658,
                                "text": "We reverse a contrary holding by the Third Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 150.52,
                                "stop": 157.115,
                                "byte_start": 705658,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has issued a dissenting opinion which justice Ginsburg has joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
